FBIS4-62461 "drsov094_b_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-094 Daily Report 14 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Issues Shakhray Says He Saw No Decree on Dismissal Shakhray Says He Saw No Decree on Dismissal LD1405141694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1259 GMT 14 May 94 LD1405141694 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Raul Tukhvatullin] [Text] Ufa May 14 TASS -- "I have not seen a presidential decree on my dismissal, so I cannot comment on reports about my dismissal," Russian Vice-prime Minister Sergey Shakhray said. The announcement followed mass media reports about Shakhray's dismissal from the post of nationalities minister. In an interview with ITAR-TASS on Saturday, Shakhray said that even if these reports turn out to be true, he will continue as vice-prime minister. Shakhray is in Ufa to attend a conference of the regional section of his party of Russian Unity and Accord. Shakhray met with Bashkir President Murtaza Rakhimov today to discuss economic problems and ways to resolve the economic crisis in Bashkiria, a Russian republic in the Volga region.
